- The "garden" refers to the educational institution;
- The "trees of knowledge" represent the courses;
- The "gardener" is the instructor;
- The "most fertile branches" indicate courses with above-average enrollment;
- The "fruits of wisdom" are the average grades of the courses;
- "Above the average yield" means the courses have more students than the average course enrollment.

- 'Flowers blooming the brightest' refers to courses with the highest average grade;
- 'Season' refers to the semester;
- 'Year' refers to the academic year.

- "Top-performing courses" are those ranked 1st in their respective semesters based on average grade;
- "A grade" includes grades A+, A, and A-;
- "Average assessment score" is calculated from all assessments in the course.

- 'Average grade' is a metric that reflects the overall performance of students in a course;
- '3.5' is a common threshold for distinguishing between good and average performance in academic settings;
- 'Fall' refers to the academic semester that typically starts in August or September.

- "star course" refers to the course with the highest average grade;
- "shines the brightest" is a metaphor for having the highest average grade;
- "academic sky" is a metaphor for the educational environment.

- "Shining stars" refers to the top 3 performing students in each course;
- "Academic garden" is a metaphor for the courses;
- "Gardeners" refers to the instructors teaching the courses.

- 'ACCY' department stands for the Accounting department;
- 'GPA' stands for Grade Point Average, a measure of academic performance;
- 'Courses' are units of study offered by the department.

- "top performers" refers to students with the highest average scores;
- "course with the identifier 1" is a specific course in the database;
- The ranking is based on the average score of the students.

- "top 5 instructors" refers to the instructors ranked highest by average course grade;
- "the academic garden" is a metaphor for the educational institution where courses are taught;
- "the flowers of knowledge bloom the brightest" metaphorically represents the highest average grades.

- "stands tall as the pinnacle of success" refers to the course offering with the highest average score;
- "shining star student" refers to the student with the highest total score in that course offering;
- "climbed to the top of this academic mountain" metaphorically describes the student who has achieved the highest score in the top-ranked course offering.
